      \DiagramSquare {
        nw = \pi _1^*E,
        sw = B\times B,
        se = B,
        ne = E,
        east/style = {|->},
        west/style = {|->,exists},
        north/style = {->,exists},
        south = \pi _1,
        height = 1.5cm,
      }
      \qquad 
      \DiagramSquare {
        nw = \pi _2^*F,
        sw = B\times B,
        se = B,
        ne = F,
        east/style = {|->},
        west/style = {|->,exists},
        north/style = {->,exists},
        south = \pi _2,
        height = 1.5cm,
      }



    The above can be seen as cartesian lift in the 2-bifibration of fibered categories over \mathbf {Cat}.

Finally, we take a cocartesian lift along the tensor functor {B\times B}\xrightarrow {{\otimes }}{B} to obtain the Day tensor:





